# Keep `CHANGELOG.md` in sync with semver bumps

`CHANGELOG.md` is the **user-facing release-notes log** (companion to
`docs/SPEC.md`'s exhaustive as-built record). It is read by the **About**
modal's "What's new" link inside the kiosk, so every bumped semver MUST have
a section in this file by the time the bumping strand merges.

Sister rule: `.cursor/rules/keep-readme-in-sync.mdc` (functional README sync).

## Trigger

Edit `CHANGELOG.md` in the **same commit** as any strand that:

- Bumps `package.json#version`'s **X** (major, breaking JSON shape) — MUST.
- Bumps `package.json#version`'s **Y** (minor, user-visible new capability) —
  MUST.
- Lands a **Z** strand whose effect is still visible to the operator
  (UI polish, animation tweak, accessibility fix, copy edit) — RECOMMENDED;
  attach to the next pending section (`[Unreleased]`).

## Skip when

- Pure internal refactor or test-only strand that doesn't change anything the
  operator can observe.
- `sonar.projectVersion` bump only (the Sonar leak baseline is independent
  from `package.json#version`).
- Planning-only strands (SPEC §17.80 / §17.82 / §17.94 pattern) — they don't
  bump `package.json#version`.

## Procedure

1. If a `[Unreleased]` section exists, promote it to the new version header
   (`## [0.Y.Z] — YYYY-MM-DD`) and re-open a fresh empty `[Unreleased]` on
   top.
2. Group entries under standard Keep-a-Changelog buckets — `Added`,
   `Changed`, `Removed`, `Deprecated`, `Fixed`, `Security`.
3. Reference the SPEC strand IDs in the entry (e.g. "(§17.87)") so a reader
   can jump to the full as-built rationale.
4. Update the comparison link footer to point the new tag at the previous
   one.

## Example

A strand that adds an "Undo last edit" button and bumps `0.2.0 → 0.3.0`:

```md
## [0.3.0] — 2026-06-01

### Added

- **Undo last edit** button on the parent identity strip (§17.99). Restores
  the previous value / objective / weight of the most recently edited node.
```

Plus the footer link gains `[0.3.0]: .../compare/v0.2.0...v0.3.0`.

## Why this is automated

The kiosk operator surfaces `CHANGELOG.md` via the About modal's link, so
"what's new in this version?" is one tap away from the focused tree. A
forgotten section turns into a dead link or an empty notes page — both
worse than the small overhead of editing the file at bump-time.
